southland <slc> unit raises crude prices
    new york, march 4 - 
southland corp's citgo petrleum corp said it raised the contract price
it will pay for all grades of crude oil by one dlr a barrel, effective
today. the increase brings citgo's posted price for west texas
intermediate to 17.00 dlrs a bbl. west texas sour is also now priced
at 17.00 dlrs/bbl, and light louisiana south is posted at 17.35
dlrs/bbl. on february 25 citgo lowered its crude postings 50 cts to
1.50 dlrs per bbl, and cut wti one dlr to 16.00. reuter 
